<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-5913] FontBox spawns a `cmd` subprocess to read an environment variable (on Windows)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5913</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FontBox&apos;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/pdfbox/blob/trunk/fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/util/autodetect/WindowsFontDirFinder.java#L43&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;`WindowsFontDirFinder`&lt;/a&gt; spawns a `cmd` subprocess to read the value of the `windir` environment variable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(It is unclear to me why it does not simply use `getenv(&quot;windir&quot;)`. Without further understanding of the context, that would be my suggested fix.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Either way, this can (and does) cause false positives in aggressive endpoint security configurations, which use &quot;spawns a shell subprocess&quot; as an indicator of process compromise.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
